:" data-popover-state="closed"><img src="./Vegetation Survey of the University of Saskatchewan Campus_files/blank-avatar.svg" alt="Your profile" class="jsx-2811423430 avatar-image"></button></div></div></div></div></header><main class="jsx-1654303428 jsx-117738961 viewer-main story-container"><article data-blockid="n-Xru4lB" class="jsx-3388570139 story"><div data-blockid="n-6znuau" id="n-6znuau" class="jsx-1050596338 layout-wrapper drag-sentinel"><div class="jsx-1903906978 full-cover-container middle"><div class="jsx-2112147785 title-panel size-large vertical-position-middle horizontal-position-center"><div class="jsx-255522243 grid-item-lite"><div class="jsx-2459931180 logo-wrapper"><img src="./Vegetation Survey of the University of Saskatchewan Campus_files/AHeWbKuibTxF__oTmUmCA.png" alt="Story logo" class="jsx-3782559711 "></div><h1 class="sc-title jsx-c4bdc700aa21a114">Vegetation Survey of the University of Saskatchewan Campus</h1><p class="jsx-3528072460 sc-summary is-viewer stacked stacked jsx-c4bdc700aa21a114">A field-based vegetation inventory conducted on the University of Saskatchewan campus, Saskatoon, Saskatchewan</p><div class="jsx-3977056478 sc-metadata"><p class="sc-byline jsx-c4bdc700aa21a114">Mohammed</p><p class="jsx-4172471729 sc-published-date viewer"><time datetime="2026-03-27T01:45:45.752Z">March 26, 2026</time></p></div></div></div><div class="jsx-2090499410 media-panel background"><figure class="jsx-194600061 jsx-3605602151 media-wrapper fill-parent"><div class="jsx-194600061 jsx-3605602151 media-wrapper-children fill-parent remove-line-height"><div class="jsx-2721836313 "><button aria-label="Attribution" aria-expanded="false" class="jsx-1837400699 icon-information jsx-957079658" aria-labelledby=":r40:" data-popover-state="closed" aria-haspopup="dialog"><span aria-hidden="true" class="jsx-3457670934 icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" class="jsx-3457670934"><path d="M7.5 2.5a1 1 0 1 1 1 1 1 1 0 0 1-1-1M9 14V5H7v1h1v8H7v1h3v-1z" class="jsx-3457670934"></path></svg></span></button></div><div data-blockid="n-dIK6IC" class="jsx-3600554988 image-container fill-parent theme-has-shape jsx-2761730200"><div class="jsx-3600554988 inner-container theme-has-shape"><img alt="Photo of University of Saskatchewan" loading="eager" id=":r3u:" class="jsx-1404764697 image jsx-3828925019 is-cropped theme-has-shape" width="1152" height="2048" src="blob:https://storymaps.arcgis.com/958a7759-17ed-4421-85e4-ef4ec2c6a819"></div></div></div></figure><div class="jsx-2090499410 mask"></div></div><div class="jsx-1903906978 icon-container"><span class="jsx-1951274455 icon icon-animating-arrow"><svg viewBox="0 0 13 42" aria-hidden="true" class="jsx-1951274455"><path d="M7 35.4h5.7l-6.3 6.3L0 35.4h6V0h1z" class="jsx-1951274455 "></path></svg></span></div></div></div><div data-blockid="n-vaCGLS" id="n-vaCGLS" class="jsx-4094307056 layout-wrapper navigation-bar  drag-sentinel"><nav data-blockid="n-vaCGLS" aria-label="Heading links" class="jsx-1710101296 navigation-viewer"><div class="jsx-234202632 bar-container"><button aria-label="Previous headings" class="jsx-2299114054 arrow left"><span aria-hidden="true" class="jsx-2447550679 icon icon-left"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" class="jsx-2447550679"><path d="M21 13H4.707l2.646 2.646-.707.707L2.793 12.5l3.853-3.854.707.707L4.707 12H21z" class="jsx-2447550679"></path></svg></span></button><ol class="jsx-234202632 content"><li class="jsx-1565966618 page-anchor-list-item"><a href="https://storymaps.arcgis.com/stories/8b5be77841d4413cac1dffc254921071#n-6FrBpe" id="l-n-6FrBpe" class="jsx-1565966618 page-anchor-link">Introduction</a></li><li class="jsx-1565966618 page-anchor-list-item"><a href="https://storymaps.arcgis.com/stories/8b5be77841d4413cac1dffc254921071#n-sWYKlx" id="l-n-sWYKlx" class="jsx-1565966618 page-anchor-link">Methodology</a></li><li class="jsx-1565966618 page-anchor-list-item"><a href="https://storymaps.arcgis.com/stories/8b5be77841d4413cac1dffc254921071#n-5eKIsf" id="l-n-5eKIsf" class="jsx-1565966618 page-anchor-link" aria-current="true">Result</a></li><li class="jsx-1565966618 page-anchor-list-item"><a href="https://storymaps.arcgis.com/stories/8b5be77841d4413cac1dffc254921071#n-9hlHFE" id="l-n-9hlHFE" class="jsx-1565966618 page-anchor-link">References</a></li></ol><button aria-label="Next headings" class="jsx-2044766557 arrow right"><span aria-hidden="true" class="jsx-2447550679 icon icon-right"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" class="jsx-2447550679"><path d="M16.646 15.646 19.293 13H3v-1h16.293l-2.647-2.646.707-.707 3.854 3.853-3.854 3.854z" class="jsx-2447550679"></path></svg></span></button></div></nav></div><div data-blockid="n-6FrBpe" id="n-6FrBpe" class="jsx-4044510251 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><div class="jsx-2836745662 text-container"><div class="jsx-2836745662 link-spacer-container"><div class="jsx-2836745662 link-spacer"><button aria-label="Copy section link" aria-describedby=":r42:" class="jsx-2836745662 link-button" data-popover-state="closed"><span aria-hidden="true" class="jsx-1135053170 icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" class="jsx-1135053170"><path d="M5 9.5a5 5 0 0 0 .048.493l-.023-.018-3-3a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95-4.95l3 3a3.486 3.486 0 0 1-1.31 5.76l-.226-.225a1.5 1.5 0 0 1-.37-.631 2.495 2.495 0 0 0 1.199-4.197l-3-3a2.5 2.5 0 1 0-3.536 3.536L5.09 8.625A4.5 4.5 0 0 0 5 9.5m11 3a3.48 3.48 0 0 0-1.025-2.475l-3-3-.023-.018A5 5 0 0 1 12 7.5a4.5 4.5 0 0 1-.089.876l2.357 2.356a2.5 2.5 0 0 1-.009 3.544 2.56 2.56 0 0 1-3.527-.008l-3-3a2.5 2.5 0 0 1-.094-3.436 2.43 2.43 0 0 1 1.3-.74 1.5 1.5 0 0 0-.377-.652l-.222-.222a3.482 3.482 0 0 0-1.314 5.757l3 3a3.5 3.5 0 0 0 4.937.012l-.351-.355.352.355A3.48 3.48 0 0 0 16 12.5" class="jsx-1135053170"></path></svg></span></button></div></div><div data-blockid="n-6FrBpe" class="jsx-781984284 text-viewer"><h2 id=":r42:" data-testid="Heading" class="jsx-2728492018 heading responsive jsx-2895946300">Introduction</h2></div></div></div></div><div data-blockid="n-FtpJg7" id="n-FtpJg7" class="jsx-1608645298 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><div data-blockid="n-FtpJg7" class="jsx-781984284 text-viewer"><p data-testid="Paragraph" class="jsx-1867417704 jsx-1394512618 medium responsive">The University of Saskatchewan (USask) campus in Saskatoon, Saskatchewan, is home to a diverse range of vegetation, including trees, shrubs, and other plant forms distributed across its expansive grounds. The main campus in Saskatoon encompasses approximately 1,865 acres of land, with about <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" data-id="4h-9eGL" href="https://leadership.usask.ca/administration/real-estate.php" class="jsx-444877590 underline-solid"><span contenteditable="false" class="jsx-1f24ab0bc0e7a45f">&nbsp;</span>40%<span contenteditable="false" class="jsx-1f24ab0bc0e7a45f">&nbsp;</span></a> dedicated to the core academic campus and related uses, situated along the South Saskatchewan River.</p></div></div></div><div data-blockid="n-BtpFjU" id="n-BtpFjU" class="jsx-1608645298 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><div data-blockid="n-BtpFjU" class="jsx-781984284 text-viewer"><p data-testid="Paragraph" class="jsx-1867417704 jsx-1394512618 medium responsive">The original campus plan centered buildings around a large green space known as The Bowl, which remains a central green feature of the campus <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" data-id="-jEeA-1" href="https://kids.kiddle.co/University_of_Saskatchewan" class="jsx-444877590 underline-solid"><span contenteditable="false" class="jsx-1f24ab0bc0e7a45f">&nbsp;</span>today<span contenteditable="false" class="jsx-1f24ab0bc0e7a45f">&nbsp;</span></a>. The campus is located in a prairie urban environment, and its green spaces support a notable variety of woody vegetation. The Patterson Garden Arboretum, located on the USask campus, has grown into one of the most compelling collections of trees, shrubs, and vines in the Canadian Prairie Provinces, situated in plant hardiness zone 3b and experiencing a continental climate with cold <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" data-id="71KWr3E" href="https://patterson-arboretum.usask.ca/" class="jsx-444877590 underline-solid"><span contenteditable="false" class="jsx-1f24ab0bc0e7a45f">&nbsp;</span>winters and hot summers<span contenteditable="false" class="jsx-1f24ab0bc0e7a45f">&nbsp;</span></a>. The campus also hosts the Patterson Arboretum, established in 1966 as part of the Prairie Regional Trials for Woody Ornamentals, providing a botanical reference collection of tree specimens hardy to <a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" data-id="2LzPU8u" href="https://gardening.usask.ca/gardening-advice/sorted-by-plant/trees.php" class="jsx-444877590 underline-solid"><span contenteditable="false" class="jsx-1f24ab0bc0e7a45f">&nbsp;</span>Zone 2b<span contenteditable="false" class="jsx-1f24ab0bc0e7a45f">&nbsp;</span></a>. Understanding the spatial distribution and physical characteristics of vegetation across the campus is valuable for environmental monitoring, landscape management, and urban green space planning.</p></div></div></div><div data-blockid="n-st6sSG" id="n-st6sSG" class="jsx-1608645298 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><div data-blockid="n-st6sSG" class="jsx-781984284 text-viewer"><p data-testid="Paragraph" class="jsx-1867417704 jsx-1394512618 medium responsive">This project presents the results of a field-based vegetation survey conducted on the University of Saskatchewan campus as part of the Introduction to GIS: Geospatial Data microcredential at Seneca Polytechnic. The survey aimed to collect data for individual vegetations (tree or shrub), recording both their geographic location and key physical attributes (listed below).</p></div></div></div><div data-blockid="n-8Pn3IK" id="n-8Pn3IK" class="jsx-2839305906 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><div class="jsx-44824658 separator-wrapper"><hr class="jsx-44824658 separator line-single"></div></div></div><div data-blockid="n-sWYKlx" id="n-sWYKlx" class="jsx-4044510251 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><div class="jsx-2836745662 text-container"><div class="jsx-2836745662 link-spacer-container"><div class="jsx-2836745662 link-spacer"><button aria-label="Copy section link" aria-describedby=":r48:" class="jsx-2836745662 link-button" data-popover-state="closed"><span aria-hidden="true" class="jsx-1135053170 icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" class="jsx-1135053170"><path d="M5 9.5a5 5 0 0 0 .048.493l-.023-.018-3-3a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95-4.95l3 3a3.486 3.486 0 0 1-1.31 5.76l-.226-.225a1.5 1.5 0 0 1-.37-.631 2.495 2.495 0 0 0 1.199-4.197l-3-3a2.5 2.5 0 1 0-3.536 3.536L5.09 8.625A4.5 4.5 0 0 0 5 9.5m11 3a3.48 3.48 0 0 0-1.025-2.475l-3-3-.023-.018A5 5 0 0 1 12 7.5a4.5 4.5 0 0 1-.089.876l2.357 2.356a2.5 2.5 0 0 1-.009 3.544 2.56 2.56 0 0 1-3.527-.008l-3-3a2.5 2.5 0 0 1-.094-3.436 2.43 2.43 0 0 1 1.3-.74 1.5 1.5 0 0 0-.377-.652l-.222-.222a3.482 3.482 0 0 0-1.314 5.757l3 3a3.5 3.5 0 0 0 4.937.012l-.351-.355.352.355A3.48 3.48 0 0 0 16 12.5" class="jsx-1135053170"></path></svg></span></button></div></div><div data-blockid="n-sWYKlx" class="jsx-781984284 text-viewer"><h2 id=":r48:" data-testid="Heading" class="jsx-2728492018 heading responsive jsx-2895946300">Methodology</h2></div></div></div></div><div data-blockid="n-mcZlwx" id="n-mcZlwx" class="jsx-1608645298 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><div data-blockid="n-mcZlwx" class="jsx-781984284 text-viewer"><p data-testid="Paragraph" class="jsx-1867417704 jsx-1394512618 medium responsive">Data was collected using ArcGIS Field Maps on a mobile device and visualized and analyzed using ArcGIS Online. The survey focused on documenting two primary plant forms, trees and shrubs, and capturing attributes such as plant height, diameter at breast height (DBH), growth status, and GPS positional accuracy for each sample point. </p></div></div></div><div data-blockid="n-0OIonU" id="n-0OIonU" class="jsx-2937103378 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><div class="jsx-1068227533 text-container"><div class="jsx-1068227533 link-spacer-container"><div class="jsx-1068227533 link-spacer"><button aria-label="Copy section link" aria-describedby=":r4c:" class="jsx-1068227533 link-button" data-popover-state="closed"><span aria-hidden="true" class="jsx-1135053170 icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" class="jsx-1135053170"><path d="M5 9.5a5 5 0 0 0 .048.493l-.023-.018-3-3a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95-4.95l3 3a3.486 3.486 0 0 1-1.31 5.76l-.226-.225a1.5 1.5 0 0 1-.37-.631 2.495 2.495 0 0 0 1.199-4.197l-3-3a2.5 2.5 0 1 0-3.536 3.536L5.09 8.625A4.5 4.5 0 0 0 5 9.5m11 3a3.48 3.48 0 0 0-1.025-2.475l-3-3-.023-.018A5 5 0 0 1 12 7.5a4.5 4.5 0 0 1-.089.876l2.357 2.356a2.5 2.5 0 0 1-.009 3.544 2.56 2.56 0 0 1-3.527-.008l-3-3a2.5 2.5 0 0 1-.094-3.436 2.43 2.43 0 0 1 1.3-.74 1.5 1.5 0 0 0-.377-.652l-.222-.222a3.482 3.482 0 0 0-1.314 5.757l3 3a3.5 3.5 0 0 0 4.937.012l-.351-.355.352.355A3.48 3.48 0 0 0 16 12.5" class="jsx-1135053170"></path></svg></span></button></div></div><div data-blockid="n-0OIonU" class="jsx-781984284 text-viewer"><h3 id=":r4c:" data-testid="Heading" class="jsx-2728492018 heading responsive jsx-2895946300">Data Collection</h3></div></div></div></div><div data-blockid="n-0le2BI" id="n-0le2BI" class="jsx-2937103378 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><div class="jsx-833223251 text-container"><div class="jsx-833223251 link-spacer-container"><div class="jsx-833223251 link-spacer"><button aria-label="Copy section link" aria-describedby=":r4f:" class="jsx-833223251 link-button" data-popover-state="closed"><span aria-hidden="true" class="jsx-1135053170 icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" class="jsx-1135053170"><path d="M5 9.5a5 5 0 0 0 .048.493l-.023-.018-3-3a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95-4.95l3 3a3.486 3.486 0 0 1-1.31 5.76l-.226-.225a1.5 1.5 0 0 1-.37-.631 2.495 2.495 0 0 0 1.199-4.197l-3-3a2.5 2.5 0 1 0-3.536 3.536L5.09 8.625A4.5 4.5 0 0 0 5 9.5m11 3a3.48 3.48 0 0 0-1.025-2.475l-3-3-.023-.018A5 5 0 0 1 12 7.5a4.5 4.5 0 0 1-.089.876l2.357 2.356a2.5 2.5 0 0 1-.009 3.544 2.56 2.56 0 0 1-3.527-.008l-3-3a2.5 2.5 0 0 1-.094-3.436 2.43 2.43 0 0 1 1.3-.74 1.5 1.5 0 0 0-.377-.652l-.222-.222a3.482 3.482 0 0 0-1.314 5.757l3 3a3.5 3.5 0 0 0 4.937.012l-.351-.355.352.355A3.48 3.48 0 0 0 16 12.5" class="jsx-1135053170"></path></svg></span></button></div></div><div data-blockid="n-0le2BI" class="jsx-781984284 text-viewer"><h4 id=":r4f:" data-testid="Heading" class="jsx-2728492018 heading responsive jsx-2895946300">Attribute Fields</h4></div></div></div></div><div data-blockid="n-Xw8CNR" id="n-Xw8CNR" class="jsx-1563605009 float-layout end layout-wrapper is-draggable"><div class="jsx-1563605009 float-wrapper end"><figure class="jsx-730557133 jsx-3605602151 media-wrapper with-caption"><div class="jsx-730557133 jsx-3605602151 media-wrapper-children remove-line-height with-themed-shape"><div class="jsx-2571299382 "><button aria-label="Attribution" aria-expanded="false" class="jsx-1837400699 icon-information jsx-957079658" aria-labelledby=":r79:" data-popover-state="closed" aria-haspopup="dialog"><span aria-hidden="true" class="jsx-3457670934 icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" class="jsx-3457670934"><path d="M7.5 2.5a1 1 0 1 1 1 1 1 1 0 0 1-1-1M9 14V5H7v1h1v8H7v1h3v-1z" class="jsx-3457670934"></path></svg></span></button></div><div class="jsx-996731563 jsx-877333076 parent"><div class="jsx-996731563 jsx-877333076 reparent-wrapper contracted with-custom-on-click"><div class="jsx-1482926022 expand-media-button-container"><span id=":r4m:" class="jsx-1482926022 visually-hidden">Photo of Field Form</span><button aria-label="Expand media" aria-describedby=":r4m:" aria-pressed="false" class="jsx-4257457771"></button></div><div data-blockid="n-Xw8CNR" class="jsx-1375385841 image-container theme-has-shape jsx-2761730200"><div class="jsx-1375385841 inner-container theme-has-shape"><img alt="Photo of Field Form" loading="lazy" id=":r4i:" class="jsx-1404764697 image jsx-513858747 theme-has-shape" width="624" height="570" src="blob:https://storymaps.arcgis.com/bb5c0b3c-5b00-4387-85cb-a79e67326b95"></div></div></div></div></div><figcaption id="caption-:r4q:" class="jsx-3232094028 jsx-842824322 caption"><p data-testid="TextInput" class="text-input"><strong data-testid="CustomText-Bold" class="jsx-5eded4394ab87caf">Figure 1: </strong>Field form designed for data collection</p></figcaption></figure></div></div><div data-blockid="n-ypn8BB" id="n-ypn8BB" class="jsx-1608645298 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><div data-blockid="n-ypn8BB" class="jsx-781984284 text-viewer"><p data-testid="Paragraph" class="jsx-1867417704 jsx-1394512618 medium responsive">The field form used for data collection was configured in ArcGIS Field Maps Designer and included the following attribute fields for each recorded sample point, as indicated in Figure 1:</p></div></div></div><div data-blockid="n-1uhXVO" id="n-1uhXVO" class="jsx-1608645298 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><div data-blockid="n-1uhXVO" class="jsx-781984284 text-viewer"><ul data-testid="BulletList" class="jsx-2682870380 generic-list bullet-list responsive medium"><li data-testid="ListItem" class="jsx-3719392474 jsx-3105765535"><strong data-testid="CustomText-Bold" class="jsx-5eded4394ab87caf">Date and Time:</strong> the date and time the sample was recorded in the field.</li></ul></div></div></div><div data-blockid="n-fu0H7B" id="n-fu0H7B" class="jsx-1608645298 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><div data-blockid="n-fu0H7B" class="jsx-781984284 text-viewer"><ul data-testid="BulletList" class="jsx-2682870380 generic-list bullet-list responsive medium"><li data-testid="ListItem" class="jsx-3719392474 jsx-3105765535"><strong data-testid="CustomText-Bold" class="jsx-5eded4394ab87caf">Plant Form:</strong> the form of the observed vegetation, classified as either a tree or a shrub. This field was set as required and used a dropdown menu to ensure consistent data entry across all samples.</li></ul></div></div></div><div data-blockid="n-tUBq7B" id="n-tUBq7B" class="jsx-1608645298 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><div data-blockid="n-tUBq7B" class="jsx-781984284 text-viewer"><ul data-testid="BulletList" class="jsx-2682870380 generic-list bullet-list responsive medium"><li data-testid="ListItem" class="jsx-3719392474 jsx-3105765535"><strong data-testid="CustomText-Bold" class="jsx-5eded4394ab87caf">Plant Growth Status:</strong> the current growth condition of the vegetation at the time of observation, recorded as either active growth or dormant. This field was set as required.</li></ul></div></div></div><div data-blockid="n-SxBqqQ" id="n-SxBqqQ" class="jsx-1608645298 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><div data-blockid="n-SxBqqQ" class="jsx-781984284 text-viewer"><ul data-testid="BulletList" class="jsx-2682870380 generic-list bullet-list responsive medium"><li data-testid="ListItem" class="jsx-3719392474 jsx-3105765535"><strong data-testid="CustomText-Bold" class="jsx-5eded4394ab87caf">Diameter at Breast Height (cm) (DBH):</strong> the estimated diameter of the vegetation stem or trunk measured at breast height (approximately 1.3 m from the ground).</li></ul></div></div></div><div data-blockid="n-scGFC1" id="n-scGFC1" class="jsx-1608645298 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><div data-blockid="n-scGFC1" class="jsx-781984284 text-viewer"><ul data-testid="BulletList" class="jsx-2682870380 generic-list bullet-list responsive medium"><li data-testid="ListItem" class="jsx-3719392474 jsx-3105765535"><strong data-testid="CustomText-Bold" class="jsx-5eded4394ab87caf">Height (m): </strong>the estimated height of the vegetation specimen recorded in meters. This field was set as required for all samples.</li></ul></div></div></div><div data-blockid="n-ovUEfC" id="n-ovUEfC" class="jsx-1608645298 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><div data-blockid="n-ovUEfC" class="jsx-781984284 text-viewer"><ul data-testid="BulletList" class="jsx-2682870380 generic-list bullet-list responsive medium"><li data-testid="ListItem" class="jsx-3719392474 jsx-3105765535"><strong data-testid="CustomText-Bold" class="jsx-5eded4394ab87caf">Horizontal Accuracy (m): </strong>the horizontal positional accuracy of the GPS location recorded by the mobile device at the time of data collection, reported in meters.</li></ul></div></div></div><div data-blockid="n-CdkEsP" id="n-CdkEsP" class="jsx-1608645298 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><div data-blockid="n-CdkEsP" class="jsx-781984284 text-viewer"><ul data-testid="BulletList" class="jsx-2682870380 generic-list bullet-list responsive medium"><li data-testid="ListItem" class="jsx-3719392474 jsx-3105765535"><strong data-testid="CustomText-Bold" class="jsx-5eded4394ab87caf">Photo:</strong> a photograph of the vegetation specimen captured in the field at the time of data collection, providing visual reference for each recorded sample.</li></ul></div></div></div><div data-blockid="n-q7UL0P" id="n-q7UL0P" class="jsx-2937103378 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><div class="jsx-1068227533 text-container"><div class="jsx-1068227533 link-spacer-container"><div class="jsx-1068227533 link-spacer"><button aria-label="Copy section link" aria-describedby=":r53:" class="jsx-1068227533 link-button" data-popover-state="closed"><span aria-hidden="true" class="jsx-1135053170 icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" class="jsx-1135053170"><path d="M5 9.5a5 5 0 0 0 .048.493l-.023-.018-3-3a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95-4.95l3 3a3.486 3.486 0 0 1-1.31 5.76l-.226-.225a1.5 1.5 0 0 1-.37-.631 2.495 2.495 0 0 0 1.199-4.197l-3-3a2.5 2.5 0 1 0-3.536 3.536L5.09 8.625A4.5 4.5 0 0 0 5 9.5m11 3a3.48 3.48 0 0 0-1.025-2.475l-3-3-.023-.018A5 5 0 0 1 12 7.5a4.5 4.5 0 0 1-.089.876l2.357 2.356a2.5 2.5 0 0 1-.009 3.544 2.56 2.56 0 0 1-3.527-.008l-3-3a2.5 2.5 0 0 1-.094-3.436 2.43 2.43 0 0 1 1.3-.74 1.5 1.5 0 0 0-.377-.652l-.222-.222a3.482 3.482 0 0 0-1.314 5.757l3 3a3.5 3.5 0 0 0 4.937.012l-.351-.355.352.355A3.48 3.48 0 0 0 16 12.5" class="jsx-1135053170"></path></svg></span></button></div></div><div data-blockid="n-q7UL0P" class="jsx-781984284 text-viewer"><h3 id=":r53:" data-testid="Heading" class="jsx-2728492018 heading responsive jsx-2895946300">Analysis</h3></div></div></div></div><div data-blockid="n-aIqzrO" id="n-aIqzrO" class="jsx-2937103378 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><div class="jsx-833223251 text-container"><div class="jsx-833223251 link-spacer-container"><div class="jsx-833223251 link-spacer"><button aria-label="Copy section link" aria-describedby=":r56:" class="jsx-833223251 link-button" data-popover-state="closed"><span aria-hidden="true" class="jsx-1135053170 icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" class="jsx-1135053170"><path d="M5 9.5a5 5 0 0 0 .048.493l-.023-.018-3-3a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95-4.95l3 3a3.486 3.486 0 0 1-1.31 5.76l-.226-.225a1.5 1.5 0 0 1-.37-.631 2.495 2.495 0 0 0 1.199-4.197l-3-3a2.5 2.5 0 1 0-3.536 3.536L5.09 8.625A4.5 4.5 0 0 0 5 9.5m11 3a3.48 3.48 0 0 0-1.025-2.475l-3-3-.023-.018A5 5 0 0 1 12 7.5a4.5 4.5 0 0 1-.089.876l2.357 2.356a2.5 2.5 0 0 1-.009 3.544 2.56 2.56 0 0 1-3.527-.008l-3-3a2.5 2.5 0 0 1-.094-3.436 2.43 2.43 0 0 1 1.3-.74 1.5 1.5 0 0 0-.377-.652l-.222-.222a3.482 3.482 0 0 0-1.314 5.757l3 3a3.5 3.5 0 0 0 4.937.012l-.351-.355.352.355A3.48 3.48 0 0 0 16 12.5" class="jsx-1135053170"></path></svg></span></button></div></div><div data-blockid="n-aIqzrO" class="jsx-781984284 text-viewer"><h4 id=":r56:" data-testid="Heading" class="jsx-2728492018 heading responsive jsx-2895946300">Positional Accuracy Assessment using Buffer Analysis</h4></div></div></div></div><div data-blockid="n-NJNciu" id="n-NJNciu" class="jsx-1608645298 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><div data-blockid="n-NJNciu" class="jsx-781984284 text-viewer"><p data-testid="Paragraph" class="jsx-1867417704 jsx-1394512618 medium responsive">To assess the positional accuracy of the collected GPS data, a buffer analysis was performed using the Create Buffers tool in ArcGIS Online Map Viewer. For each of the 25 collected sample points, a buffer zone was generated using the Horizontal Accuracy (m) field recorded at the time of data collection as the buffer distance.</p></div></div></div><div data-blockid="n-CWheqP" id="n-CWheqP" class="jsx-2937103378 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><div class="jsx-833223251 text-container"><div class="jsx-833223251 link-spacer-container"><div class="jsx-833223251 link-spacer"><button aria-label="Copy section link" aria-describedby=":r5a:" class="jsx-833223251 link-button" data-popover-state="closed"><span aria-hidden="true" class="jsx-1135053170 icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" class="jsx-1135053170"><path d="M5 9.5a5 5 0 0 0 .048.493l-.023-.018-3-3a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95-4.95l3 3a3.486 3.486 0 0 1-1.31 5.76l-.226-.225a1.5 1.5 0 0 1-.37-.631 2.495 2.495 0 0 0 1.199-4.197l-3-3a2.5 2.5 0 1 0-3.536 3.536L5.09 8.625A4.5 4.5 0 0 0 5 9.5m11 3a3.48 3.48 0 0 0-1.025-2.475l-3-3-.023-.018A5 5 0 0 1 12 7.5a4.5 4.5 0 0 1-.089.876l2.357 2.356a2.5 2.5 0 0 1-.009 3.544 2.56 2.56 0 0 1-3.527-.008l-3-3a2.5 2.5 0 0 1-.094-3.436 2.43 2.43 0 0 1 1.3-.74 1.5 1.5 0 0 0-.377-.652l-.222-.222a3.482 3.482 0 0 0-1.314 5.757l3 3a3.5 3.5 0 0 0 4.937.012l-.351-.355.352.355A3.48 3.48 0 0 0 16 12.5" class="jsx-1135053170"></path></svg></span></button></div></div><div data-blockid="n-CWheqP" class="jsx-781984284 text-viewer"><h4 id=":r5a:" data-testid="Heading" class="jsx-2728492018 heading responsive jsx-2895946300">Plant Analysis</h4></div></div></div></div><div data-blockid="n-2BMs0w" id="n-2BMs0w" class="jsx-1608645298 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><div data-blockid="n-2BMs0w" class="jsx-781984284 text-viewer"><p data-testid="Paragraph" class="jsx-1867417704 jsx-1394512618 medium responsive">A Plant Form Distribution chart was produced to illustrate the breakdown of the 25 collected samples by plant form, showing the proportion of trees (17 points) versus shrubs (8 points) recorded across the campus. Additionally, a Plant Growth Status chart was created to show the proportion of vegetation specimens recorded as either active growth or dormant at the time of the survey.</p></div></div></div><div data-blockid="n-WBPPEq" id="n-WBPPEq" class="jsx-2839305906 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><div class="jsx-44824658 separator-wrapper"><hr class="jsx-44824658 separator line-single"></div></div></div><div data-blockid="n-5eKIsf" id="n-5eKIsf" class="jsx-4044510251 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><div class="jsx-2836745662 text-container"><div class="jsx-2836745662 link-spacer-container"><div class="jsx-2836745662 link-spacer"><button aria-label="Copy section link" aria-describedby=":r5e:" class="jsx-2836745662 link-button" data-popover-state="closed"><span aria-hidden="true" class="jsx-1135053170 icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" class="jsx-1135053170"><path d="M5 9.5a5 5 0 0 0 .048.493l-.023-.018-3-3a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95-4.95l3 3a3.486 3.486 0 0 1-1.31 5.76l-.226-.225a1.5 1.5 0 0 1-.37-.631 2.495 2.495 0 0 0 1.199-4.197l-3-3a2.5 2.5 0 1 0-3.536 3.536L5.09 8.625A4.5 4.5 0 0 0 5 9.5m11 3a3.48 3.48 0 0 0-1.025-2.475l-3-3-.023-.018A5 5 0 0 1 12 7.5a4.5 4.5 0 0 1-.089.876l2.357 2.356a2.5 2.5 0 0 1-.009 3.544 2.56 2.56 0 0 1-3.527-.008l-3-3a2.5 2.5 0 0 1-.094-3.436 2.43 2.43 0 0 1 1.3-.74 1.5 1.5 0 0 0-.377-.652l-.222-.222a3.482 3.482 0 0 0-1.314 5.757l3 3a3.5 3.5 0 0 0 4.937.012l-.351-.355.352.355A3.48 3.48 0 0 0 16 12.5" class="jsx-1135053170"></path></svg></span></button></div></div><div data-blockid="n-5eKIsf" class="jsx-781984284 text-viewer"><h2 id=":r5e:" data-testid="Heading" class="jsx-2728492018 heading responsive jsx-2895946300">Result</h2></div></div></div></div><div data-blockid="n-VV82d2" id="n-VV82d2" class="jsx-2937103378 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><div class="jsx-1068227533 text-container"><div class="jsx-1068227533 link-spacer-container"><div class="jsx-1068227533 link-spacer"><button aria-label="Copy section link" aria-describedby=":r5h:" class="jsx-1068227533 link-button" data-popover-state="closed"><span aria-hidden="true" class="jsx-1135053170 icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" class="jsx-1135053170"><path d="M5 9.5a5 5 0 0 0 .048.493l-.023-.018-3-3a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95-4.95l3 3a3.486 3.486 0 0 1-1.31 5.76l-.226-.225a1.5 1.5 0 0 1-.37-.631 2.495 2.495 0 0 0 1.199-4.197l-3-3a2.5 2.5 0 1 0-3.536 3.536L5.09 8.625A4.5 4.5 0 0 0 5 9.5m11 3a3.48 3.48 0 0 0-1.025-2.475l-3-3-.023-.018A5 5 0 0 1 12 7.5a4.5 4.5 0 0 1-.089.876l2.357 2.356a2.5 2.5 0 0 1-.009 3.544 2.56 2.56 0 0 1-3.527-.008l-3-3a2.5 2.5 0 0 1-.094-3.436 2.43 2.43 0 0 1 1.3-.74 1.5 1.5 0 0 0-.377-.652l-.222-.222a3.482 3.482 0 0 0-1.314 5.757l3 3a3.5 3.5 0 0 0 4.937.012l-.351-.355.352.355A3.48 3.48 0 0 0 16 12.5" class="jsx-1135053170"></path></svg></span></button></div></div><div data-blockid="n-VV82d2" class="jsx-781984284 text-viewer"><h3 id=":r5h:" data-testid="Heading" class="jsx-2728492018 heading responsive jsx-2895946300">Collected Data</h3></div></div></div></div><div data-blockid="n-fatNli" id="n-fatNli" class="jsx-1608645298 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><div data-blockid="n-fatNli" class="jsx-781984284 text-viewer"><p data-testid="Paragraph" class="jsx-1867417704 jsx-1394512618 medium responsive">Field data was collected on March 20, 2026, using ArcGIS Field Maps on a mobile device. A total of 25 vegetation sample points were recorded across the campus, consisting of 17 tree points and 8 shrub points. They are visualized on the map below.</p></div></div></div><div data-blockid="n-MNn8XT" id="n-MNn8XT" class="jsx-2839305906 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><figure class="jsx-3035897356 jsx-3605602151 media-wrapper with-caption"><div class="jsx-3035897356 jsx-3605602151 media-wrapper-children remove-line-height with-themed-shape"><div class="jsx-4114551332 jsx-3621986332 full-screen-wrapper"><div class="jsx-4114551332 jsx-3621986332 overlay"><div class="jsx-4114551332 jsx-3621986332 full-screen-button-container"><button class="button single-icon themed-control icon-button button-styles with-border with-background large jsx-1128713261 icon-button jsx-774070654" type="button"><div class="icon-wrapper jsx-774070654"><span aria-hidden="true" class="jsx-3457670934 icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" class="jsx-3457670934"><path d="M15 15h-4v-1h2.282l-3.633-3.584.767-.767L14 13.282V11h1zM5 1v1H2.718l3.633 3.584-.767.767L2 2.718V5H1V1z" class="jsx-3457670934"></path></svg></span><span class="visually-hidden">Expand</span></div></button></div><div role="none" class="jsx-646041069 map-wrapper web-map-viewer-container"><div aria-label="" role="application" data-item-id="549a6833d83f4c35b1052310b068ec2d" data-blockid="n-MNn8XT" class="jsx-203acf9d2744b046 jsx-755654564 arcgis-map-container esri-view-width-medium esri-view-width-greater-than-xsmall esri-view-width-greater-than-small esri-view-width-less-than-large esri-view-width-less-than-xlarge esri-view-height-xsmall esri-view-height-less-than-small esri-view-height-less-than-medium esri-view-height-less-than-large esri-view-height-less-than-xlarge esri-view-orientation-landscape esri-view"><div class="esri-view-root"><div class="esri-view-surface esri-view-surface--touch-none" role="application" tabindex="0"><canvas style="width: 827px; height: 465px; display: block;" width="620" height="349"></canvas></div><div class="esri-overlay-surface"><div style="visibility: hidden;"></div></div><div dir="ltr" class="esri-widget esri-view-attribution esri-attribution calcite-mode-light">
      <div class="esri-attribution__sources esri-interactive" tabindex="0">City of Saskatoon | Vantor | Esri Canada | The study area for this project is located on the University of Saskatchewan campus in Saskatoon, Saskatchewan. Field data was collected using ArcGIS Field Maps, and the feature layer was created, configured, and hosted using ArcGIS Online, both provided by Esri Canada. Basemap and reference data were sourced from the Esri Living Atlas of the World and include contributions from Esri Canada, TomTom, Garmin, NASA, NRCan, and Parks Canada. This project was completed as part of the Introduction to GIS: Geospatial Data micro-credential program at Seneca Polytechnic.</div>
