7103378 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><div class="jsx-833223251 text-container"><div class="jsx-833223251 link-spacer-container"><div class="jsx-833223251 link-spacer"><button aria-label="Copy section link" aria-describedby=":r63:" class="jsx-833223251 link-button" data-popover-state="closed"><span aria-hidden="true" class="jsx-1135053170 icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" class="jsx-1135053170"><path d="M5 9.5a5 5 0 0 0 .048.493l-.023-.018-3-3a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95-4.95l3 3a3.486 3.486 0 0 1-1.31 5.76l-.226-.225a1.5 1.5 0 0 1-.37-.631 2.495 2.495 0 0 0 1.199-4.197l-3-3a2.5 2.5 0 1 0-3.536 3.536L5.09 8.625A4.5 4.5 0 0 0 5 9.5m11 3a3.48 3.48 0 0 0-1.025-2.475l-3-3-.023-.018A5 5 0 0 1 12 7.5a4.5 4.5 0 0 1-.089.876l2.357 2.356a2.5 2.5 0 0 1-.009 3.544 2.56 2.56 0 0 1-3.527-.008l-3-3a2.5 2.5 0 0 1-.094-3.436 2.43 2.43 0 0 1 1.3-.74 1.5 1.5 0 0 0-.377-.652l-.222-.222a3.482 3.482 0 0 0-1.314 5.757l3 3a3.5 3.5 0 0 0 4.937.012l-.351-.355.352.355A3.48 3.48 0 0 0 16 12.5" class="jsx-1135053170"></path></svg></span></button></div></div><div data-blockid="n-u98xjX" class="jsx-781984284 text-viewer"><h4 id=":r63:" data-testid="Heading" class="jsx-2728492018 heading responsive jsx-2895946300">Plant Growth Status</h4></div></div></div></div><div data-blockid="n-0wOMte" id="n-0wOMte" class="jsx-1608645298 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><div data-blockid="n-0wOMte" class="jsx-781984284 text-viewer"><p data-testid="Paragraph" class="jsx-1867417704 jsx-1394512618 medium responsive">Given that the survey was conducted on March 20, 2026, growth initiation season in Saskatoon, a significant portion of the recorded vegetation was still in a dormant state (Chart 2). This is particularly evident among the tree specimens, which tend to show visible signs of active growth later in the season compared to some shrub species (illustrated in the map below). The Plant Growth Status chart 2 above shows the proportion of active growth versus dormant specimens recorded across all 25 sample points.</p></div></div></div><div data-blockid="n-rJPtSG" id="n-rJPtSG" class="jsx-2839305906 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><figure class="jsx-2479184217 jsx-3605602151 media-wrapper with-caption"><div class="jsx-2479184217 jsx-3605602151 media-wrapper-children remove-line-height with-themed-shape"><div class="jsx-4232392255 "><button aria-label="Attribution" aria-expanded="false" class="jsx-1837400699 icon-information jsx-957079658" aria-labelledby=":r69:" data-popover-state="closed" aria-haspopup="dialog"><span aria-hidden="true" class="jsx-3457670934 icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" class="jsx-3457670934"><path d="M7.5 2.5a1 1 0 1 1 1 1 1 1 0 0 1-1-1M9 14V5H7v1h1v8H7v1h3v-1z" class="jsx-3457670934"></path></svg></span></button></div><div class="jsx-996731563 jsx-877333076 parent"><div class="jsx-996731563 jsx-877333076 reparent-wrapper contracted with-custom-on-click"><div class="jsx-1482926022 expand-media-button-container"><span id=":r6b:" class="jsx-1482926022 visually-hidden">Chart 3</span><button aria-label="Expand media" aria-describedby=":r6b:" aria-pressed="false" class="jsx-4257457771"></button></div><div data-blockid="n-rJPtSG" class="jsx-3732013332 image-container theme-has-shape jsx-2761730200"><div class="jsx-3732013332 inner-container theme-has-shape"><img alt="Chart 3" loading="lazy" id=":r67:" class="jsx-1404764697 image jsx-513858747 theme-has-shape" width="2043" height="1552" src="blob:https://storymaps.arcgis.com/8c499d02-f17a-48fb-a406-b7fea6f16bff"></div></div></div></div></div><figcaption id="caption-:r6f:" class="jsx-3232094028 jsx-842824322 caption"><p data-testid="TextInput" class="text-input">Plant Count by Form and Growth Status</p></figcaption></figure></div></div><div data-blockid="n-wrLmi6" id="n-wrLmi6" class="jsx-2937103378 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><div class="jsx-833223251 text-container"><div class="jsx-833223251 link-spacer-container"><div class="jsx-833223251 link-spacer"><button aria-label="Copy section link" aria-describedby=":r6g:" class="jsx-833223251 link-button" data-popover-state="closed"><span aria-hidden="true" class="jsx-1135053170 icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" class="jsx-1135053170"><path d="M5 9.5a5 5 0 0 0 .048.493l-.023-.018-3-3a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95-4.95l3 3a3.486 3.486 0 0 1-1.31 5.76l-.226-.225a1.5 1.5 0 0 1-.37-.631 2.495 2.495 0 0 0 1.199-4.197l-3-3a2.5 2.5 0 1 0-3.536 3.536L5.09 8.625A4.5 4.5 0 0 0 5 9.5m11 3a3.48 3.48 0 0 0-1.025-2.475l-3-3-.023-.018A5 5 0 0 1 12 7.5a4.5 4.5 0 0 1-.089.876l2.357 2.356a2.5 2.5 0 0 1-.009 3.544 2.56 2.56 0 0 1-3.527-.008l-3-3a2.5 2.5 0 0 1-.094-3.436 2.43 2.43 0 0 1 1.3-.74 1.5 1.5 0 0 0-.377-.652l-.222-.222a3.482 3.482 0 0 0-1.314 5.757l3 3a3.5 3.5 0 0 0 4.937.012l-.351-.355.352.355A3.48 3.48 0 0 0 16 12.5" class="jsx-1135053170"></path></svg></span></button></div></div><div data-blockid="n-wrLmi6" class="jsx-781984284 text-viewer"><h4 id=":r6g:" data-testid="Heading" class="jsx-2728492018 heading responsive jsx-2895946300">Plant Count by Form and Growth Status</h4></div></div></div></div><div data-blockid="n-SRdnyt" id="n-SRdnyt" class="jsx-1608645298 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><div data-blockid="n-SRdnyt" class="jsx-781984284 text-viewer"><p data-testid="Paragraph" class="jsx-1867417704 jsx-1394512618 medium responsive">The above chart illustrates the distribution of plant growth status across the two recorded vegetation forms. Among the 17 tree specimens, the majority were classified as dormant (10 trees), while 7 were recorded as showing active growth. Among the 8 shrub specimens, the opposite pattern was observed, with 6 shrubs showing active growth and only 2 recorded as dormant.</p></div></div></div><div data-blockid="n-OYNiEP" id="n-OYNiEP" class="jsx-1608645298 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><div data-blockid="n-OYNiEP" class="jsx-781984284 text-viewer"><p data-testid="Paragraph" class="jsx-1867417704 jsx-1394512618 medium responsive">Overall, dormancy was more prevalent among trees, which may reflect the slower seasonal response of larger woody vegetation in the early growing season. The higher proportion of active growth among shrubs suggests that some shrub species on the University of Saskatchewan campus had already begun their growth cycle at the time of the survey on March 20, 2026. These findings are consistent with expected early growth vegetation conditions in Saskatoon, Saskatchewan, where temperatures are still transitioning from winter and vegetation response varies by species and size.</p></div></div></div><div data-blockid="n-6FuCih" id="n-6FuCih" class="jsx-2937103378 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><div class="jsx-833223251 text-container"><div class="jsx-833223251 link-spacer-container"><div class="jsx-833223251 link-spacer"><button aria-label="Copy section link" aria-describedby=":r6l:" class="jsx-833223251 link-button" data-popover-state="closed"><span aria-hidden="true" class="jsx-1135053170 icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" class="jsx-1135053170"><path d="M5 9.5a5 5 0 0 0 .048.493l-.023-.018-3-3a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95-4.95l3 3a3.486 3.486 0 0 1-1.31 5.76l-.226-.225a1.5 1.5 0 0 1-.37-.631 2.495 2.495 0 0 0 1.199-4.197l-3-3a2.5 2.5 0 1 0-3.536 3.536L5.09 8.625A4.5 4.5 0 0 0 5 9.5m11 3a3.48 3.48 0 0 0-1.025-2.475l-3-3-.023-.018A5 5 0 0 1 12 7.5a4.5 4.5 0 0 1-.089.876l2.357 2.356a2.5 2.5 0 0 1-.009 3.544 2.56 2.56 0 0 1-3.527-.008l-3-3a2.5 2.5 0 0 1-.094-3.436 2.43 2.43 0 0 1 1.3-.74 1.5 1.5 0 0 0-.377-.652l-.222-.222a3.482 3.482 0 0 0-1.314 5.757l3 3a3.5 3.5 0 0 0 4.937.012l-.351-.355.352.355A3.48 3.48 0 0 0 16 12.5" class="jsx-1135053170"></path></svg></span></button></div></div><div data-blockid="n-6FuCih" class="jsx-781984284 text-viewer"><h4 id=":r6l:" data-testid="Heading" class="jsx-2728492018 heading responsive jsx-2895946300">Positional Accuracy</h4></div></div></div></div><div data-blockid="n-62VZH2" id="n-62VZH2" class="jsx-1608645298 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><div data-blockid="n-62VZH2" class="jsx-781984284 text-viewer"><p data-testid="Paragraph" class="jsx-1867417704 jsx-1394512618 medium responsive">The buffer map below illustrates the spatial distribution of positional accuracy across all collected sample points on the University of Saskatchewan campus. Overall, the buffers demonstrate that the GPS accuracy achieved during the survey was reasonable for a mobile device in an open campus environment, though some variation is observed across sample locations.</p></div></div></div><div data-blockid="n-ncSwpL" id="n-ncSwpL" class="jsx-2839305906 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-255522243 grid-item-lite"><figure class="jsx-3874525262 jsx-3605602151 media-wrapper with-caption"><div class="jsx-3874525262 jsx-3605602151 media-wrapper-children remove-line-height with-themed-shape"><div class="jsx-4114551332 jsx-3621986332 full-screen-wrapper"><div class="jsx-4114551332 jsx-3621986332 overlay"><div class="jsx-4114551332 jsx-3621986332 full-screen-button-container"><button class="button single-icon themed-control icon-button button-styles with-border with-background large jsx-1128713261 icon-button jsx-774070654" type="button"><div class="icon-wrapper jsx-774070654"><span aria-hidden="true" class="jsx-3457670934 icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" class="jsx-3457670934"><path d="M15 15h-4v-1h2.282l-3.633-3.584.767-.767L14 13.282V11h1zM5 1v1H2.718l3.633 3.584-.767.767L2 2.718V5H1V1z" class="jsx-3457670934"></path></svg></span><span class="visually-hidden">Expand</span></div></button></div><div role="none" class="jsx-646041069 map-wrapper web-map-viewer-container"><div aria-label="" role="application" data-item-id="549a6833d83f4c35b1052310b068ec2d" data-blockid="n-ncSwpL" class="jsx-203acf9d2744b046 jsx-755654564 arcgis-map-container esri-view-width-xlarge esri-view-width-greater-than-xsmall esri-view-width-greater-than-small esri-view-width-greater-than-medium esri-view-width-greater-than-large esri-view-height-small esri-view-height-greater-than-xsmall esri-view-height-less-than-medium esri-view-height-less-than-large esri-view-height-less-than-xlarge esri-view-orientation-landscape"><div class="jsx-2619305305 jsx-338101261"></div><div class="jsx-95fbf4cdbfd99c13 arcgis-map-info-popup-container"></div><div class="jsx-1359446143 jsx-929827813"></div><div tabindex="0" role="button" class="jsx-1359446143 jsx-929827813 arcgis-map-info-legend-container esri-legend esri-widget esri-widget--panel" style="display: inline-flex;"><button aria-label="Close" class="jsx-1543589790 corner-button override-corner-placement"><span aria-hidden="true" class="jsx-3457670934 icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" class="jsx-3457670934"><path d="M3.98 11.303 7.281 8 3.98 4.697l.707-.707L7.99 7.293l.01-.01.01.01 3.304-3.303.707.707L8.718 8l3.303 3.303-.707.707L8.01 8.707l-.01.01-.01-.01-3.304 3.303z" class="jsx-3457670934"></path></svg></span></button><div class="esri-legend__message">No legend</div></div></div></div></div></div></div><figcaption id="caption-:r6r:" class="jsx-3232094028 caption"><p data-testid="TextInput" class="text-input">Buffer map representing the horizontal accuracy of collected GPS points (Note: This map uses scale-dependent labelling and layers — zooming in will reveal additional labels and feature layers for a more detailed view. Labels were configured using Arcade expression language in ArcGIS Online to control the display of vegetation attributes dynamically across zoom levels)</p></figcaption></figure></div></div><div data-blockid="n-SasK2V" id="n-SasK2V" class="jsx-1608645298 layout-wrapper"><div class="jsx-1766271777 grid-item-lite"><div data-blockid="n-SasK2V" class="jsx-781984284 text-viewer"><p data-testid="Paragraph" class="jsx-1867417704 jsx-1394512618 medium responsive">The following Arcade expression was used in the web map:</p></div></div></div><div data-blockid="n-Q26HvA" id="n-